File and Directory Navigation:
pwd: Prints the current working directory.
ls: Lists the contents of a directory.
cd [directory]: Changes the current directory to the specified directory.
mkdir [directory_name]: Creates a new directory.
rmdir [directory_name]: Removes an empty directory.
File Operations:
touch [file_name]: Creates an empty file or updates the timestamp of an existing file.
cp [source] [destination]: Copies files or directories.
mv [source] [destination]: Moves or renames files or directories.
rm [file_name]: Deletes files. Use rm -r [directory_name] to delete directories and their contents.
cat [file_name]: Displays the content of a file.
Permissions and Ownership:
chmod [permissions] [file/directory]: Changes the permissions of a file or directory.
chown [owner:group] [file/directory]: Changes the owner and group of a file or directory.
System Information and Utilities:
man [command]: Displays the manual page for a specified command.
clear: Clears the terminal screen.
echo [text]: Prints text to the terminal.
grep [pattern] [file]: Searches for a pattern within a file.
sudo [command]: Executes a command with superuser privileges.
